.TH "asd_chip_reset" 9 "asd_chip_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
asd_chip_reset \- - reset the host adapter, etc
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" asd_chip_reset
.BI "(struct asd_ha_struct *asd_ha "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "asd_ha" 12
pointer to host adapter structure of interest
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called from the ISR.  Hard reset the chip.  Let everything
timeout.  This should be no different than hot-unplugging the
host adapter.  Once everything times out we'll init the chip with
a call to \fBasd_init_chip\fP and enable interrupts with \fBasd_enable_ints\fP.
